  "title": "Corrective fix for B-267580f8: Test shared semantic memory integration end to end",
  "agent_type": "developer",
  "description": "Blocked reason: memory.py:search() fails at runtime with 'sqlite3.OperationalError: A LIMIT or k = ? constraint is required on vec0 knn queries.' on Python 3.14 / sqlite-vec 0.1.9 / SQLite 3.51.3. The implementation uses 'LIMIT ?' SQL parameter binding but this version of sqlite-vec requires 'AND k = ?' in the WHERE clause instead. All 16 search-dependent tests fail. Fix: in memory.py around line 393, change 'WHERE v.embedding MATCH ? ORDER BY v.distance LIMIT ?' to 'WHERE v.embedding MATCH ? AND k = ? ORDER BY v.distance' (same parameter tuple, just reordered semantics).\n\nRemaining work: Developer fix required: memory.py:search() must replace 'LIMIT ?' with 'AND k = ?' in the sqlite-vec KNN query WHERE clause. Once fixed, all 16 failing tests will pass.",
